a

credit <-read.csv("credit.csv", header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = TRUE)
sapply(credit, is.factor)
    checking_balance months_loan_duration       credit_history              purpose               amount      savings_balance  employment_duration 
                TRUE                FALSE                 TRUE                 TRUE                FALSE                 TRUE                 TRUE 
   percent_of_income   years_at_residence                  age         other_credit              housing existing_loans_count                  job 
               FALSE                FALSE                FALSE                 TRUE                 TRUE                FALSE                 TRUE 
          dependents                phone              default 
               FALSE                 TRUE                 TRUE 
# Stratified sampling with the rsample package
set.seed(123)
split <- initial_split(credit, prop = 0.7, 
                       strata = "default")
default_train  <- training(split)
default_test   <- testing(split)
# Specify resampling strategy
cv <- trainControl(
  method = "repeatedcv", 
  number = 10, 
  repeats = 5
)
# Create grid of hyperparameter values
hyper_grid <- expand.grid(k = seq(30, 80, by = 1))

# Tune a knn model using grid search
knn_fit <- train(
  default ~ . , 
  data = default_train, 
  method = "knn", 
  trControl = cv, 
  tuneGrid = hyper_grid,
  metric = "Accuracy" 
)

knn_fit$bestTune
finalModel<- knn_fit$finalModel
ggplot(knn_fit)

defaultPred <- predict(knn_fit, default_test, type="prob")
plot(defaultPred$yes~default, data=default_test)
